description:
In this remarkable film, a child's malicious lie destroys the lives of two young teachers. The child lies to avoid school because &quot;everyone there hates me.&quot; The lie is believed because it is compounded by idle ramblings. Then it is upheld by a girl who is lying only to protect herself. This piece plays remarkably well today as it shows that children do lie even when they don't really know what they are talking about. Audrey Hepburn and Shirley MacLaine are remarkable in this work as they show the emotional upheaval that a simple lie can cause. 

